Yes, there were some warning signs before the eruption of the Rabaul volcano in 1994. The volcano had been showing increased activity for several weeks before the eruption occurred, with seismic activity and the formation of a new vent on the volcano's flank. 

Local authorities had been monitoring the situation and had implemented evacuation plans for the surrounding communities. Despite this, the eruption caused widespread damage and loss of life, highlighting the unpredictability of volcanic activity and the challenges involved in managing the risks associated with living near an active volcano.
